sn't reversed yet.\" The bot correctly blocked.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 23:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Shadow Data CONFIRMS: Excluded Hours = 49% WR (Coin Flip)\n\n**Task:** Analyze shadow trade outcomes from excluded hours.\n\n**Shadow trade outcomes (Mar 31, n=45):**\n| Hour | W/L | WR | Note |\n|------|-----|----|------|\n| 1h | 1/0 | 100% | n=1, ignore |\n| 3h | 1/2 | 33% | Asian = bad |\n| 6h | 1/4 | **20%** | Asian end = terrible |\n| 8h | 0/5 | **0%** | Pre-London = DISASTER |\n| 10h | 3/1 | 75% | V6 candidate? n=4 |\n| 14h | 2/2 | 50% | Coin flip (US open) |\n| 16h | 3/0 | 100% | V6 candidate? n=3 |\n| **ALL** | **22/23** | **49%** | **BELOW BREAKEVEN** |\n\n**Active hours [11,12,19,20]: 100% WR (n=1 today, n=29 over V4.1 lifetime = 83% WR)**\n**Excluded hours (shadow): 49% WR (n=45) = COIN FLIP MINUS FEES = NET LOSER**\n\nThis is the strongest validation yet for hour selection. Our 4-hour window isn't leaving money on the table \u2014 the other hours literally produce random noise.\n\n**V6 hour candidates (TENTATIVE, need n\u226520 each):**\n- 10h UTC (75%, n=4): Pre-11h, might capture early London momentum\n- 16h UTC (100%, n=3): US afternoon, might capture post-15h recover",
